quieted funeral bells~
The bell-naming convention matches the schema used in the Nightfall Catacombs' chapel bells, the same four categories in the same order with the same color attributions: silver for intake, bronze for adjudication, crimson for lament, and black for reclamation. The Nightfall bell tradition is ancient; the Ossuary has adopted it in its entirety while removing all functional capability from the bells. The tradition is preserved as display, stripped of its acoustic authority. The cathedral preserves the form while eliminating the function; this is the null-seal principle applied to memorial music.
~
