The walls of this corridor are lined with @@Wnightglass panels@@N, a material processed from bone ash and silica that produces a translucent glass with a faint luminescence visible only in very low light. The panels have been installed here as a final visual preparation before the closing chambers: their faint glow creates a boundary between the procedural sections of the wing and the terminal zone ahead. A series of small @@Wfunerary attestation markers@@N are embedded in the nightglass, each marker indicating a specific doctrinal category and its relationship to the final rite.
~
