funerary attestation markers~
The attestation markers follow the Compact-era civic format for funerary documentation, adapted to the Ossuary's eclipse doctrine. Each marker's doctrinal category corresponds to a different outcome for the subject: some lead to archive, some to reassignment, and one, the category marked with the null symbol, leads to what the marker calls "doctrinal resolution." The same word used on the Reliquary's wax faces. The outcome behind that word is not documented on the marker itself.
