#5723
@@WPenumbral Last Rite@@N~
The penultimate chamber of the Moonbone wing serves as the formal threshold for the final rite, its walls carved with the complete Moonbone Ossuary protocol for terminal proceedings. The protocol is dense and specific, describing every step of the process by which a subject's doctrinal status is finalized, their posthumous jurisdiction assigned, and their administrative utility determined. At the north end of the chamber, a @@Wviolet threshold@@N stands sealed, a gate of combined violet-iron and bone-glass whose lock requires the @@Wviolet threshold key@@N to open. Somewhere below the formal protocol inscriptions, an older text is visible, letters worn nearly smooth: the Kel'Shadra funeral oath, "What is witnessed must be named," scraped over with the Ossuary's own protocol but not fully erased.
~
