#5701
Lady Noctyra, Mirrored Censer Regent~
@@mLady Noctyra, Mirrored Censer Regent@@N~
@@mLady Noctyra@@N stands at the center of her Reliquary, a curved obsidian mirror raised before her like a second face.
~
Lady Noctyra of the Mirrored Censer transformed reliquary etiquette into statecraft. She did not fight during the Silenced Vespers; she observed. While others argued over whether to publish contradictory ledgers, she studied how the ledgers themselves conferred power. Her insight was not ethical but structural: whoever controls the classification system controls reality's admissible facts. The mirrored censers she carries â originally surveillance tools designed to observe relic petitioners without direct eye contact â were adopted as the Amethyst Reliquary's signature instruments by her successors. Her rotating censer still swings in the reliquary nave, maintained by current staff who claim it moves by her lingering will. Whether this is doctrine or misdirection is unclear. Noctyra would find the ambiguity appropriate.
~
