#5702
Abbot Vharos, Null-Halo Archivist~
@@dAbbot Vharos, Null-Halo Archivist@@N~
@@dAbbot Vharos@@N stands surrounded by rotating rings of obsidian-lacquered metal, each one a null-seal in continuous motion.
~
Abbot Vharos is the cathedral's most intellectually dangerous inhabitant. He arrived from outside â the only major officeholder known to have joined after the withdrawal rather than surviving through it â and brought two innovations that transformed the institution: the null-seal system that renders documents administratively nonexistent without physical destruction, and the tri-sign witness locks borrowed from the Gloamvault's Sepulcher Descent. His rotating halos are not theatrical accessories; they are working demonstrations of the null-seal principle, rings of obsidian that continuously orbit whatever they hover over, symbolically eclipsing it. To stand in their shadow is to feel the specific discomfort of existing in a space where institutional authority makes you technically unreal.
~
