#5704
the Violet Hierophant~
@@mthe Violet Hierophant@@N~
@@mThe Violet Hierophant@@N sits upon the Moonbone Throne, their identity wholly subsumed into the office they have become.
~
The Violet Hierophant is not a person. The person who once occupied this title â who had a name, a life before the cathedral, origins outside its doctrine â has been eclipsed by their own governance apparatus. The office has consumed the officeholder so completely that the individual's history has itself been eclipsed: removed from the active registry not temporarily but permanently and irreversibly. The Hierophant sits on the Moonbone Throne, a seat constructed from the processed remains of previous officeholders whose precedents were deemed worthy of permanent institutional memory. To issue a judgment from this throne is to speak with the voice of every predecessor whose bones compose it. When they speak, the sentence that emerges is simultaneously the most personal statement they are capable of making and the most institutional: a mechanism, not a person, declaring what the past is allowed to have meant.
~
