The keystone was the architectural capstone of the cathedral's central nave before it fell. The eclipse symbol carved into it â full disc, crescent shadow, the founding image of the institution's doctrine â was designed to be readable from ground level only in certain light conditions, when shadows cast by the rose windows fell at the correct angle. In that light, the keystone's shadow would project the eclipse symbol onto the nave floor, marking the exact center of the cathedral's spatial authority. The keystone no longer hangs above anything. The shadow no longer falls.
~
